Step 1 :  sudo apt update
Step 2 : Install wget
Command : sudo apt install -y wget

Step 3 : wget https://dev.mysql.com/get/mysql-apt-config_0.8.15-1_all.deb

Step 4 : sudo dpkg -i mysql-apt-config_0.8.15-1_all.deb

Step 5 : Select ubuntu bionic and ok

Step 6 :  sudo apt update

Step 7 : Install mysql 
Command : sudo apt install mysql-community-server

Step 8 : Enable and check the status of the mysql service
Command : sudo systemctl enable --now mysql
          sudo systemctl status --mysql

Step 9 : sudo mysql -u root -p
